                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "GDByj",
                      "name": "Para 1",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 760,
                      "content": "Gerrit Cole has been virtually untouchable in his last five starts, posting a 2.41 ERA with 42 strikeouts across 37.1 innings. The Red Sox rank 28th in the majors against right-handed pitching this month, batting just .228 with a .296 OBP — a matchup that heavily favors New York's ace.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "nveOc",
                  "name": "ParaWrap 2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "padding": [
                    0,
                    0,
                    16,
                    0
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "yVP01",
                      "name": "Para 2",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 760,
                      "content": "On the other side, Brayan Bello enters with a 4.22 ERA and has struggled to generate swing-and-miss against playoff-caliber lineups. The Yankees offense, led by Aaron Judge (.301, 18 HR) and Juan Soto (.289, 14 HR), should find gaps in Bello's above-average contact rate.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "XMpqW",
                  "name": "ParaWrap 3",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "padding": [
                    0,
                    0,
                    16,
                    0
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "MAN9e",
                      "name": "Para 3",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 760,
                      "content": "Fenway Park's dimensions tend to inflate left-handed power numbers, and the Yankees possess three of the top left-handed hitters in the AL. The wind is forecast to blow out to right-center at 12 mph, adding to the offensive upside for New York's lineup.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
